The paper deals with the problem of segmenting high-dimensional structural data, which is a common problem in machine learning and computer vision. The use of spectral clustering and sparse reconstruction techniques suggests that the paper may belong to the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision), or cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). The focus on low-rank representation and positive semidefinite constraints suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-categories of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) or cs.NA (Numerical Analysis).
